			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Fading in Fear yet again<a name="73042"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 9 05 10:27 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I had the &quot;pleasure&quot; of spending a few hours in the Plane of Fear trying to help a fair sized group recover the corpses they had littering the plane.  The group was a bit too small, and did not have the needed tanks to really *hold* a camp in Fear, so it would get messy.
<br />

<br />
Of course, the Enraged Imp came to play, which meant that not long after, the Ireblind Imp was there camping the corpses.
<br />

<br />
I had occasion to try and use Fading Memories several times.  Sometimes it worked, sometimes it didn't.  As nearly as I can figure, what was going on is that Fade does not work at all on mobs that can see invis in the Plane of Fear.
<br />

<br />
I could be half way across the zone from a mob, completely out of line of sight for it, and well outside normal agro range, and hit Fade to no avail.  The thing would show up a few moments later, usually with a bunch of other critters.
<br />

<br />
I note that the Ireblind Imp, and all the Enraged Imps he spawns, can see invis.  I tried a few different times to kite him away from the corpses, and then fade so as to park him in a new spot.  I've read in the Guides here on this site about doing this.  It didn't work at all.  I killed all his buddies and pulled him all by himself over to a nice isolated spot, ran out away from him and faded, only to have him keep right on coming after me.
<br />

<br />
The Imp loses interest in you when he hits you with his AoE stun.  He'd get me with that, and then go right back to camping all the corpses.  We ended up having two teams.  One would pull the imp and kite him around, the other would run in and drag corpses away from the Imp's favorite spot.
<br />

<br />
Does this match what other people have observed?  Is it only in Fear, or have they made it so that Fade does not work on See Invis mobs at all anywhere?</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
