				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Fading in Fear yet again<a name="73044"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 9 05 11:53 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ireblind can be your friend, too, courtesy of his AE stun, since it isn't just him that is blurred, but everything that has aggro on you.  Mana-free fade without the invis, at the cost of a few seconds of movement.
<br />

<br />
As far as Fade, as far as I know, it always works... but with the see-invis mobs and aggro range, the only time you can relax is once the zone is cleared.  Even that isn't totally safe, as we found out once.  
<br />

<br />
Cleared almost all of the zone, heading off to the next mob when our buddy CT spawned, and reset the zone, along with repopping all the trash we'd cleared.  Of course, people'd gotten strung out while moving, etc.  So, a significant CR later, we left CT alone for a day.
<br />

<br />
Cheers,
<br />
Grith</span></td>
