				<td colspan="2"><span>I think in his example what happened is that the raid set up
<br />
at a camp, probably on the west wall, and that's where they
<br />
spawned the Ire Imp.  That becomes his spawn point.  So even
<br />
if you run himto the opposite side of the zone and fade, he will
<br />
still eventually path back to your camp, re-aggro'ing as soon
<br />
as he sees you guys, so it looks like aggro was never lost.
<br />

<br />
The trick to dealing with him is that when you get the enraged
<br />
imp, pull him far away from raid, kill him, and then go back to
<br />
raid.  You'll have Ireblind imp up, but he won't path to your
<br />
raid.
<br />

<br />
Fleeing mob vs. fade bug exists, but needs some very specific
<br />
things to occur for it to show itself, so rarely a factor.
<br />

<br />
'Stuce</span></td>
